From 6c2ab5e3b82730939be19e70b7c5204a016fb12d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: abracodeabra1 <abrahampaul.elenjical@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 19:13:11 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] ggml : add LNS (Logarithmic Number System) backend

Adds a new ggml backend that performs LLM inference using 16-bit
Logarithmic Number System (xlns16) arithmetic via the xlnscpp library.

Core ggml changes:
- ggml.h: add GGML_TYPE_LNS16 = 41, bump GGML_TYPE_COUNT to 42
- ggml.c: register LNS16 type traits; make type_traits[] non-const so
  ggml_backend_lns_reg() can patch to_float/from_float at runtime
- CMakeLists.txt: add GGML_LNS option (default OFF)
- src/CMakeLists.txt: add ggml_add_backend(LNS)
- src/ggml-backend-reg.cpp: register LNS backend under GGML_USE_LNS

New backend (ggml/src/ggml-lns/):
- Implements 13 ops: MUL_MAT, ADD, MUL, SCALE, SOFT_MAX, RMS_NORM,
  DIAG_MASK_INF, SILU, GELU, RELU, GET_ROWS, CPY/CONT/DUP, ROPE
- Weights converted dynamically from quantized formats per row
- Activations kept in xlns16 between ops; FP only at boundaries

Build with: cmake .. -DGGML_LNS=ON -DGGML_METAL=OFF
Requires xlnscpp at XLNSCPP_DIR (default: ../../../../xlnscpp)

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
